obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25730)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25730&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Prohibition of Child`
  line `Marriage Act, 2006.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***; and it applies also to all citizens of India without and beyond`
  line `India:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this Act shall apply to the Renoncants of the Union territory of`
  line Pondicherry.
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different States and any reference in`
  line `any provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed in relation to any State as a reference`
  line `to the coming into force of that provision in that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. 1st November, 2007, vide notification No. S.O. 1850(E), dated 30th October, 2007, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25731)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25731&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "child" means a person who, if a male, has not completed twenty-one years of age, and if a`
  line `female, has not completed eighteen years of age;`
  line
  line `(b) "child marriage" means a marriage to which either of the contracting parties is a child;`
  line
  line `(c) "contracting party", in relation to a marriage, means either of the parties whose marriage is or`
  line `is about to be thereby solemnised;`
  line
  line `(d) "Child Marriage Prohibition Officer" includes the Child Marriage Prohibition Officer`
  line `appointed under sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(e) "district court" means, in any area for which a Family Court established under section 3 of the`
  line `Family Courts Act, 1984 (66 of 1984) exists, such Family Court, and in any area for which there is no`
  line `Family Court but a city civil court exists, that court and in any other area, the principal civil court of`
  line `original jurisdiction and includes any other civil court which may be specified by the State`
  line `Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, as having jurisdiction in respect of the matters`
  line `dealt with in this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "minor" means a person who, under the provisions of the Majority Act, 1875 (9 of 1875), is to`
  line `be deemed not to have attained his majority.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25732)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Child marriages to be voidable at the option of contracting party being a child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25732&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `child marriage, whether solemnised before or after the commencement of this Act, shall be voidable at the`
  line `option of the contracting party who was a child at the time of the marriage:`
  line
  line `Provided that a petition for annulling a child marriage by a decree of nullity may be filed in the`
  line `district court only by a contracting party to the marriage who was a child at the time of the marriage.`
  line
  line `(2) If at the time of filing a petition, the petitioner is a minor, the petition may be filed through his or`
  line `her guardian or next friend along with the Child Marriage Prohibition Officer.`
  line
  line `(3) The petition under this section may be filed at any time but before the child filing the petition`
  line `completes two years of attaining majority.`
  line
  line `(4) While granting a decree of nullity under this section, the district court shall make an order`
  line `directing both the parties to the marriage and their parents or their guardians to return to the other party,`
  line `his or her parents or guardian, as the case may be, the money, valuables, ornaments and other gifts`
  line `received on the occasion of the marriage by them from the other side, or an amount equal to the value of`
  line `such valuables, ornaments, other gifts and money:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order under this section shall be passed unless the concerned parties have been given`
  line `notices to appear before the district court and show cause why such order should not be passed.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Substitution of section 3.--In the Prohibition of Child Marriage Act, 2006 (Central Act 6 of 2007)`
  line `(hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), In section 3, after sub-section (1) the following shall be`
  line `inserted, namely;--`
  line
  line `“(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) every child marriage solemnized on or`
  line `after the date of coming into force of the Prohibition of Child Marriage (Karnataka Amendment) Act,`
  line `2016 shall be void abinitio”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 26 of 2017, s. 2].`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25733)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Provision for maintenance and residence to female contracting party to child marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25733&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `While granting a decree under section 3, the district court may also make an interim or final order`
  line `directing the male contracting party to the child marriage, and in case the male contracting party to such`
  line `marriage is a minor, his parent or guardian to pay maintenance to the female contracting party to the`
  line `marriage until her remarriage.`
  line
  line `(2) The quantum of maintenance payable shall be determined by the district court having regard to the`
  line `needs of the child, the lifestyle enjoyed by such child during her marriage and the means of income of the`
  line `paying party.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount of maintenance may be directed to be paid monthly or in lump sum.`
  line
  line `(4) In case the party making the petition under section 3 is the female contracting party, the district`
  line `court may also make a suitable order as to her residence until her remarriage.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25734)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Custody and maintenance of children of child marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25734&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where there are children born of`
  line `the child marriage, the district court shall make an appropriate order for the custody of such children.`
  line
  line `(2) While making an order for the custody of a child under this section, the welfare and best interests`
  line `of the child shall be the paramount consideration to be given by the district court.`
  line
  line `(3) An order for custody of a child may also include appropriate directions for giving to the other`
  line `party access to the child in such a manner as may best serve the interests of the child, and such other`
  line `orders as the district court may, in the interest of the child, deem proper.`
  line
  line `(4) The district court may also make an appropriate order for providing maintenance to the child by a`
  line `party to the marriage or their parents or guardians.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25735)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Legitimacy of children born of child marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25735&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that a child marriage has`
  line `been annulled by a decree of nullity under section 3, every child begotten or conceived of such marriage`
  line `before the decree is made, whether born before or after the commencement of this Act, shall be deemed to`
  line `be a legitimate child for all purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25736)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of district court to modify orders issued under section 4 or section 5.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25736&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The district court`
  line `shall have the power to add to, modify or revoke any order made under section 4 or section 5 and if there`
  line `is any change in the circumstances at any time during the pendency of the petition and even after the final`
  line `disposal of the petition.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25737)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Court to which petition should be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25737&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of grant of reliefs under sections 3, 4`
  line `and 5, the district court having jurisdiction shall include the district court having jurisdiction over the`
  line `place where the defendant or the child resides, or where the marriage was solemnised or where the parties`
  line `last resided together or the petitioner is residing on the date of presentation of the petition.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25738)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Punishment for male adult marrying a child.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25738&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being a male adult above eighteen`
  line `years of age, contracts a child marriage shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment which may`
  line `extend to two years or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 9.--In section 9 of the principal Act, for the words “be punishable with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment which may extend to two years”, the words “be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment of not less one year which may extend up to two years” shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 26 of 2017, s. 3].`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25739)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Punishment for solemnising a child marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25739&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Whoever performs, conducts, directs or abets`
  line `any child marriage shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment which may extend to two years and`
  line `shall be liable to fine which may extend to one lakh rupees unless he proves that he had reasons to believe`
  line `that the marriage was not a child marriage.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 10.--In section 10 of the principal Act, for the words "be punishable with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment which may extend to two years, the words "be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment of not less than one year which may extend up to two years" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 26 of 2017, s. 4].`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25740)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Punishment for promoting or permitting solemnisation of child marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25740&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a`
  line `child contracts a child marriage, any person having charge of the child, whether as parent or guardian or any other person or in any other capacity, lawful or unlawful, including any member of an organisation or`
  line `association of persons who does any act to promote the marriage or permits it to be solemnised, or`
  line `negligently fails to prevent it from being solemnised, including attending or participating in a child`
  line `marriage, shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment which may extend to two years and shall also`
  line `be liable to fine which may extend up to one lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no woman shall be punishable with imprisonment.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, it shall be presumed, unless and until the contrary is proved, that`
  line `where a minor child has contracted a marriage, the person having charge of such minor child has`
  line `negligently failed to prevent the marriage from being solemnised.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 11.--In section 11 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "be punishable with rigorous imprisonment which may extend to two years", the`
  line `words be punishable with a rigorous imprisonment of not less than one year which may extend up to two`
  line `years" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(b) proviso shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 26 of 2017, s. 5].`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25741)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Marriage of a minor child to be void in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25741&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Where a child, being a`
  line minor--
  line
  line `(a) is taken or enticed out of the keeping of the lawful guardian; or`
  line
  line `(b) by force compelled, or by any deceitful means induced to go from any place; or`
  line
  line `(c) is sold for the purpose of marriage; and made to go through a form of marriage or if the minor`
  line `is married after which the minor is sold or trafficked or used for immoral purposes,`
  line
  line `such marriage shall be null and void.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25742)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of court to issue injunction prohibiting child marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25742&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in this Act, if, on an application of the Child Marriage Prohibition`
  line `Officer or on receipt of information through a complaint or otherwise from any person, a Judicial`
  line `Magistrate of the first class or a Metropolitan Magistrate is satisfied that a child marriage in contravention`
  line `of this Act has been arranged or is about to be solemnised, such Magistrate shall issue an injunction`
  line `against any person including a member of an organisation or an association of persons prohibiting such`
  line marriage.
  line
  line `(2) A complaint under sub-section (1) may be made by any person having personal knowledge or`
  line `reason to believe, and a non-governmental organisation having reasonable information, relating to the`
  line `likelihood of taking place of solemnisation of a child marriage or child marriages.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court of the Judicial Magistrate of the first class or the Metropolitan Magistrate may also take`
  line `suomotu cognizance on the basis of any reliable report or information.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of preventing solemnisation of mass child marriages on certain days such as`
  line `AkshayaTrutiya, the District Magistrate shall be deemed to be the Child Marriage Prohibition Officer with`
  line `all powers as are conferred on a Child Marriage Prohibition Officer by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) The District Magistrate shall also have additional powers to stop or prevent solemnisation of child`
  line `marriages and for this purpose, he may take all appropriate measures and use the minimum force required.`
  line
  line `(6) No injunction under sub-section (1) shall be issued against any person or member of any`
  line `organisation or association of persons unless the Court has previously given notice to such person,`
  line `members of the organisation or association of persons, as the case may be, and has offered him or them an`
  line `opportunity to show cause against the issue of the injunction:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of any urgency, the Court shall have the power to issue an interim injunction`
  line `without giving any notice under this section.`
  line
  line `(7) An injunction issued under sub-section (1) may be confirmed or vacated after giving notice and`
  line `hearing the party against whom the injunction was issued.`
  line
  line `(8) The Court may either on its own motion or on the application of any person aggrieved, rescind or`
  line `alter an injunction issued under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(9) Where an application is received under sub-section (1), the Court shall afford the applicant an`
  line `early opportunity of appearing before it either in person or by an advocate and if the Court, after hearing`
  line `the applicant rejects the application wholly or in part, it shall record in writing its reasons for so doing.`
  line
  line `(10) Whoever knowing that an injunction has been issued under sub-section (1) against him disobeys`
  line `such injunction shall be punishable with imprisonment of either description for a term which may extend`
  line `to two years or with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees or with both:`
  line
  line `Provided that no woman shall be punishable with imprisonment.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 13.--In section 13 of the principal Act, in sub-section (10), --`
  line
  line `(a) for the words "of either description for a term which may extend to two years", the words with a`
  line `minimum term of one year, which may extent up to two years" shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `(b) proviso shall be omitted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 26 of 2017, s. 6].`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25743)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Child marriages in contravention of injunction orders to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25743&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any child marriage`
  line `solemnised in contravention of an injunction order issued under section 13, whether interim or final, shall`
  line `be void ab initio.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (25744)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Offences to be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25744&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an offence punishable under this Act shall be cognizable and`
  line non-bailable.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 15A.--In the principal Act, after section 15, the following shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `“15A. Police Officer to take cognizance of an offence suo-motto.--Every Police Officer shall take`
  line `cognizance of an offence committed in his jurisdiction under this Act, suo motto.”`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 26 of 2017, s. 7].`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (25745)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Child Marriage Prohibition Officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25745&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint for the whole State, or such part thereof as may be specified in that notification,`
  line `an officer or officers to be known as the Child Marriage Prohibition Officer having jurisdiction over the`
  line `area or areas specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may also request a respectable member of the locality with a record of`
  line `social service or an officer of the Gram Panchayat or Municipality or an officer of the Government or any`
  line `public sector undertaking or an office bearer of any non-governmental organisation to assist the Child`
  line `Marriage Prohibition Officer and such member, officer or office bearer, as the case may be, shall be`
  line `bound to act accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be the duty of the Child Marriage Prohibition Officer--`
  line
  line `(a) to prevent solemnisation of child marriages by taking such action as he may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(b) to collect evidence for the effective prosecution of persons contravening the provisions of this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(c) to advise either individual cases or counsel the residents of the locality generally not to`
  line `indulge in promoting, helping, aiding or allowing the solemnisation of child marriages;`
  line
  line `(d) to create awareness of the evil which results from child marriages;`
  line
  line `(e) to sensitize the community on the issue of child marriages;`
  line
  line `(f) to furnish such periodical returns and statistics as the State Government may direct; and`
  line
  line `(g) to discharge such other functions and duties as may be assigned to him by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, invest the Child Marriage Prohibition Officer with such powers of a police officer as may be`
  line `specified in the notification and the Child Marriage Prohibition Officer shall exercise such powers subject`
  line `to such conditions and limitations, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(5) The Child Marriage Prohibition Officer shall have the power to move the Court for an order under`
  line `sections 4, 5 and 13 and along with the child under section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (25746)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Child Marriage Prohibition Officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25746&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Child Marriage Prohibition`
  line `Officers shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (25747)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25747&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Child Marriage Prohibition Officer in respect of anything in good faith done or intended to`
  line `be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (25748)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25748&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before the State`
  line Legislature.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (25749)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Amendment of Act No. 25 of 1955.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25749&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `In the Hindu Marriage Act, 1955, in section 18, for clause`
  line `(a), the following clause shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(a) in the case of contravention of the condition specified in clause (iii) of section 5, with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment which may extend to two years or with fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees, or with both".`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (25750)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592&sectionId=25750&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_13_14_00001_200706_1517807317592
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Child Marriage Restraint Act, 1929 (19 of 1929) is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, all cases and other proceedings pending or continued under the said`
  line `Act at the commencement of this Act shall be continued and disposed of in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the repealed Act, as if this Act had not been passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
